Reference: Deputy Director of Education, Amravati Division, Amravati. Go to the letter 27/09/2022.
The Proposal:
Urdu run by Balapur Minority Education and Social Welfare Society, Balapur District Akola
High School, Chittoda Ta. Khamgaon, Dist. Buldana, an unaided secondary school of Urdu medium (Class 9th to
10th) To transfer the management of the school to the Growth Power Multipurpose Society, Akola.
The proposal received under the reference letter was under the consideration of the government.
The government's decision:
To transfer the management of the school to Growth Power Multipurpose Society Akola.
The Government has decided to grant approval on the following terms and conditions: -
(1) The condition of minimum marks of the school where the management has changed shall be relaxed for any reason.
No.
(2) In the case of a school where the management has changed, any of the terms and conditions of the Government permission / approval
Care should be taken to ensure that there are no changes.
(3) From time to time, in respect of schools, teachers / non-teaching staff, salary / non-salary grants, students, etc. by the Government.
The new body will be bound to comply with the prescribed Acts, Rules, Orders, etc.
(4) These Management Changes, Government Decisions, Department of School Education and Sports, No: Mashah 2011 / (210/11)
MASHI-3 shall come into force in accordance with the rules and procedures prescribed on 17th February, 2012.
(5) Fresh complaints to the Government or to the field officers of the Education Department regarding this change of management.
if it is received or noticed that a breach of the terms and conditions regarding the change of management has occurred, or
Service allowance of teachers / non-teaching staff working in the institution before the change of management is breached by the new institution.
If so, the government will have the power to cancel the transfer.
Government Decision Number: Mashah-3124 / Q. 362/24 SM-1
The Divisional Deputy Director of Education, Amravati Division, Amravati examined all the aspects and the above.
Further action on change of management of the school, including necessary conditions in addition to terms / conditions 15
Do it within days and report it to the government.
